did.abstract: Records of the professional nursing association of King County, Washington

bioghist.p: The King County Nurses Association (KCNA) is a professional association of registered nurses, established in 1903 as the King County Graduate Nurses Association and renamed in 1951. It is affiliated on the state and national levels with the Washington State Nurses Association and the American Nurses Association. While the Washington State Nurses Association, of which KCNA is affiliated, functions as both a professional association and a union that collectively bargains for its members, KCNA functions primarily as a professional association that engages in advocacy work. KCNA also maintains a registry of its members and makes referrals to hospitals in need of nursing staff and provides continuing education opportunities for its members, collaborates with other health organizations in King County, and is active in lobbying activities.

Directors of the KCNA:
Julia O. Crose, approx. 1950s-1960s
Margaret Scharnickel, 1970s
Alma Ware, approx. 1980s-1990s

scopecontent.p: This accession spans the years 1959-1989 and documents the activities of the King County Nurses Association membership, Executive Board, special interest groups, and committees. Records include correspondence; committee and board meeting agendas, minutes, and meeting motions; convention records from KCNA, the Washington State Nurses Association, and American Nurses Association; financial documents; membership records; press, publicity, and published material from KCNA or affiliated organizations; records from continuing education and other programming KCNA sponsored or participated in; reports; awards nominations; and subject files with information on nursing and other health related issues.

See the arrangement note for a detailed list of records groups and series. When needed, additional scope and content information is included at the subgroup or series level in the box/folder inventory.

arrangement.p: The collection is arranged into 15 subgroups based on the part of KCNA that the records originated from, and then into series and subseries when applicable. Subgroup 1 contains the main office files of the organization while the remaining subgroups contain records created and/or used by the Executive Board, specific committees, or organizations that included representatives from KCNA.

processinfo.p: Processed by Emma Sommerseth, Elaine Kim, Haiyan Wang, and Crystal Rodgers in 2018-2019.

Students completed the initial rehousing and inventorying of the collection. Processing Archivist Crystal Rodgers addressed security concerns as well as preservation issues identified by the students, enhanced folder titles as needed, developed and implemented a proposed intellectual and physical arrangement of the collection, and updated the archival finding aid which previously contained only a minimally described PDF inventory.

Redactions and Discards: CERP worksheets in SERIES 9 contained social security numbers. Due to volume, only a sampling of these worksheets were kept and redacted, discarding the originals. Personnel sign-in sheets and daily logs of hours worked were discarded; however program and meeting attendance sign-in sheets were kept. Records in the Financial Records series were weeded extensively, discarding invoices and itemized receipts for individual purchases and parking vouchers due to low research value and/or bank account information. Any records in this series that demonstrated other organizational activity related to financial decisions were maintained.
